abstract: Analysis by Kaiser Family Foundation finds that half of households that received subsidies to help pay health insurance premiums in 2014 under Affordable Care Act will probably have to repay some of that money to federal government.
lead_paragraph: Half of the households that received subsidies to help pay health insurance premiums last year under the Affordable Care Act will probably have to repay some of that money to the federal government, according to a new analysis by the Kaiser Family Foundation.

headline.main: Many Will Need to Repay Health Subsidies
headline.print_headline: Many Will Need to Repay Portion of Health Subsidies
